 and residential property values: the influence of proximity, visual cues and public information (1999) Papers in Regional Science, 78, pp. 403-421; Ek, K., Public and private attitudes towards ""green"" electricity: the case of Swedish wind power (2005) Energy Policy, 33, pp. 1677-1689; Fenichel, E., Lupi, F., Hoehn, J., Kaplowitz, M., Split-sample tests of 'no opinion' responses in an attribute based choice model (2009) Land Economics, 85, pp. 349-363; Fleischer, A., Sternberg, M., The economic impact of global climate change on Mediterranean rangeland ecosystems: a space-for-time approach (2006) Ecological Economics, 59, pp. 287-295; Goett, A.A., Hudson, K., Train, K.E., Customers' choice among retail energy suppliers: the willingness-to-pay for service attributes (2000) Energy Journal, 21, pp. 1-28; Greene, W.H., Econometric Analysis (2003) Pretince-Hall; Haar, L., Stanciu, L.N., Comment upon ""Public goods and private interests: understanding non-residential demand for green power"" (2002) Energy Policy, 30, pp. 1357-1361; Hartman, R.S., Doane, M.J., Woo, C.K., Consumer rationality and the status-quo (1991) Quarterly Journal of Economics, 106, pp. 141-162; Hensher, D.A., Measurement of the valuation of travel time savings (2001) Journal of Transport Economics and Policy, 35, pp. 71-98; Hoehn, J., Lupi, F., Kaplowitz, M., Complexity in stated choice experiments: the effect of information formats on estimated variances and choice parameters (2010) Journal of Agriculture and Resource Economics, 35, pp. 568-590; Johnson, F.R., Desvousges, W.H., Estimating stated preferences with rated-pair data: environmental, health, and employment effects of energy programs (1997) Journal of Environmental Economics and Management, 34, pp. 79-99; Kaplowitz, M., Frank, L., Hoehn, J., Multiple-methods of developing and evaluating a stated preference survey for valuing wetland ecosystems (2004) Questionnaire Development, Evaluation, and Testing Methods, pp. 503-524. , Wiley, New Jers